Quote: <i>porokaiwhiria n</i> -s [Maori <i>porokaiwhiri</i>] : a small or shrubby New Zealand tree (<i>Hedycarya arborea</i>) of the family Monimiaceae with opposite short-petioled leaves and inconspicuous flowers in axillary panicles followed by bright red drupes
